In [65]:
random_direction_1 = (np.random.rand(3) - 0.5)
random_direction_2 = (np.random.rand(3) - 0.5)

print(random_direction_1,random_direction_2)

def dynamics(x, a, epsilon1, epsilon2):
    global random_direction_1, random_direction_2
    if x[0] < a[0]:
        nonlinearity = epsilon1*random_direction_1*np.sin(2*np.pi*x[0])
    else:
        nonlinearity = epsilon2*random_direction_2*np.sin(2*np.pi*x[0])
        
    return (x + a + nonlinearity) % 1

# test
x = np.array([0.1,0.2,0.9])
a = np.array([np.sqrt(2),np.sqrt(3),np.pi])%1
dynamics(x, a,0,0)

In [66]:
def orbit(x,n,a,epsilon1,epsilon2):
    sol = np.zeros(shape = [n,3])
    sol[0,:] = x
    for i in range(1,n):
        sol[i,:] = dynamics(sol[i-1,:], a, epsilon1, epsilon2)
    return sol
